    {
      "id": "REG-PUBLISH-BEGIN-QUERY-EXEC-001",
      "title": "Static publish executes #+BEGIN_QUERY blocks (title + bounded results) through the same public-only capability as {{query}}; rows filtered as non-public are reported as a count only, and malformed payloads fail closed (no raw payload in HTML or the search index)",
      "family": "privacy",
      "sources": {
        "issues": [],
        "commits": []
      },
      "platforms": [
        "all"
      ],
      "layer": "core-native",
      "status": "covered",
      "coverage": {
        "tests": [
          "crates/tine-core/src/publish.rs"
        ],
        "scenario": "publish.begin-query-execution-public-capability",
        "failBefore": "proven"
      },
      "notes": "Martin-approved Q2 delta (2026-07-21 sweep). Publish already ran {{query}} via render_query with publish_page_allowed filtering; BEGIN_QUERY containers were inert source. Now: whole-container detection mirrors the frontend BeginQuery.tsx contract (delimiters, balanced EDN, :title string, :query vector); the query source is sliced from raw and delegated to the existing bounded/cached render_query; the publication snapshot includes ALL freshly parsed pages so omitted private matches can be counted honestly, while HTML hydration capability remains public-only; a muted query-omitted note reports the count (all-pages-public never shows it); malformed containers render an inert alert and their payload is excluded from the search index; print keeps its whole-graph behavior. Fail-before (worker-run, Sol/high): 2 publish_begin_query tests fail pre-fix. Full publish suite 34 pass + whole tine-core 514 pass (manager-run)."
    },
